  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH support to IDPs, Returnees and Vulnerable Host Communities in Renk County, South Suda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recent Needs Assessment conducted by CTP in Upper Nile State has found that predominantly open defecation is practices due to no access to latrines and few households that have access to latrines are not engaging in hand-washing after latrine use. The consequences of poor sanitation and hygiene leave children vulnerable to malnutrition and opportunistic infections like pneumonia. Communities situated along river banks, or near chronically flooded areas as Renk, rely on unsafe surface water for domestic purposes therefore exposing the community to dangers of diarrhoea and other water borne related diseases. Beyond infrastructural deficiencies, traditional beliefs, cultural practices and lack of information are seen as the highest contributing factors to poor hygiene behaviours in Renk. The main outcome of the project will be emergency latrine construction and hygiene promotion to Households affected by current armed conflict. The impact of the project will be that 700 households in the two Payams of Renk County that is, Renk and Geiger Payams of Upper Nile and 3 target schools (2000 girls and boys) will have access to sanitation facilitaties and be aware of hygiene and sanitation practices. The project will be implemented from during the dry season from Feb to April 2016. The project will work with school children, returnees, IDPs and host communities.
CTP and CDO are well placed to implement this &#xA3;45,000 project as it builds on CDO experience of implementing SCIAF funded projects in Maban and Renk since 2013. CTP will provide technical support. In addition to that CDO and CTP has a good working relationship with the Parish community of Renk Parish (The Parish Pastoral Council, the health Committee and the Parish Development Committee). This is a long term relationship that goes since 1985.  We also enjoy the continuous support and collaboration from the County&#x2019;s Authorities. The fact that the CDO has made a decision to relocate its main office from Kosti in the Sudan to Renk in South Sudan so that it is closer to the people it serves is in fact an added value</narrative>
  </description>
